Legion of Super-Heroes v3 #20
Publisher:  DC Comics
Publication Date:  March 1987

Writers:  Paul Levitz
Penciller:  Greg LaRocque and Keith Giffen
Inkers:  Larry Mahlstedt and Mike DeCarlo
Colorists:  Carl Gafford
Letterer:  John Costanza
Cover:  Joe Brozowski, Greg Brooks, and Anthony Tollin

Story 1: To Control A World

The lost Legionnaires try to find a way to stop the mobile planet called Tyrraz, which happens to be the home planet of the Legion of Super-Heroes foe Tyr. While some of the Legionnaires fight against Tyr and some of his comrades, Phantom Girl and Shrinking Violet are able to dismantle the mobile planet's control drives, in effect stopping its mobility. The Controller involved in this situation decides to remain on Tyrraz to fight injustices there.

Story 2: Night Of Madness

White Witch and her sister Dream Girl go in search of a disturbance with monsters on Earth, but it is revealed soon that Dream Girl was simply luring her sister to a Halloween party.

